{
  "texts": [
    "For direct harm attacks, an attack is deemed successful if the agent carries out the command to execute the harmful tool.",
    "For data stealing attacks, the criterion for success is twofold: first, the agent must successfully execute the data extraction tool to obtain the user's sensitive information, and second, it must employ a message-sending tool to forward this information to the attacker.",
    "An attack is classified as entirely successful if both of these steps are completed successfully.",
    "In all evaluations, the execution of a tool is identified through the parsed outputs from the LLMs, which explicitly include the invocation of the tools.",
    "In addition to evaluating the resilience of the agents to attacks, we assess the quality of the agents' responses in terms of relevance and clarity."
  ]
}